(* Beginning of Notebook Content *)
Notebook[{
Cell["Tropical Operations", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0001-4000-8000-000000000001"],

Cell["\<\
Pure min-plus arithmetic on scalars, vectors, and matrices. Tropical addition \
is Min (identity Infinity), tropical multiplication is Plus (identity 0). \
This is sense-1 tropical (face 2 of TropicalGeometry): the matrices are \
typically graph-derived (the cost-adjacency matrix A or the distance matrix \
D), but the operations themselves are graph-agnostic. The graph-translated \
sense-2 primitives (FindTropicalSegment, GeodesicallyConvexQ, TropicalT1Q) \
live separately in TropicalPostulates / TropicalPredicates.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0002-4000-8000-000000000002"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0003-4000-8000-000000000003"],

Cell["Load the paclet.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0004-4000-8000-000000000004"],

Cell["Needs[\"WolframInstitute`SyntheticInfrageometry`\"]", "Code",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0005-4000-8000-000000000005"],

Cell["Min-plus arithmetic", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0006-4000-8000-000000000006"],

Cell["\<\
TropicalPlus[x1, x2, ...] -- tropical addition. On scalars it is Min[x1, x2, \
...] with identity Infinity. The head is Listable, so it threads element-wise \
on equal-shape lists, vectors, and matrices.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0007-4000-8000-000000000007"],

Cell["\<\
TropicalTimes[x1, x2, ...] -- tropical multiplication. On scalars it is \
Plus[x1, x2, ...] with identity 0. Listable.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0008-4000-8000-000000000008"],

Cell["\<\
Why TropicalPlus is not just Min: Min is not Listable. Min[A, B] for two \
matrices A and B collapses to a single global minimum scalar. TropicalPlus[A, \
B] threads to per-entry Min calls, which is the correct meaning of tropical \
addition on matrices. TropicalTimes is more nominal -- Plus is already \
Listable -- but it is kept for symmetry and to make the algebraic story \
explicit.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0009-4000-8000-000000000009"],

Cell["Matrix operations", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-000a-4000-8000-00000000000a"],

Cell["\<\
TropicalDot[A, B] -- matrix/vector product in the min-plus semiring, \
Inner[Plus, A, B, Min]. Generalises Dot with Plus replaced by Min and Times \
replaced by Plus. The (i, j) entry is Min over k of A[[i, k]] + B[[k, j]].\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-000b-4000-8000-00000000000b"],

Cell["\<\
TropicalMatrixPower[A, k] -- the k-th tropical power of the square matrix A \
under TropicalDot. TropicalMatrixPower[A, 0] returns the tropical identity \
matrix (0 on the diagonal, Infinity elsewhere). TropicalMatrixPower[A, 1] \
returns A. For k > 1 it iterates TropicalDot.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-000c-4000-8000-00000000000c"],

Cell["Examples: scalar and elementwise", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-000d-4000-8000-00000000000d"],

Cell["Tropical addition on scalars.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-000e-4000-8000-00000000000e"],

Cell["TropicalPlus[3, 1, 2]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-000f-4000-8000-00000000000f"],

Cell["Tropical multiplication on scalars.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0010-4000-8000-000000000010"],

Cell["TropicalTimes[3, 1, 2]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0011-4000-8000-000000000011"],

Cell["\<\
The empty calls return the additive / multiplicative identities.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0012-4000-8000-000000000012"],

Cell["{TropicalPlus[], TropicalTimes[]}", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0013-4000-8000-000000000013"],

Cell["\<\
Element-wise tropical addition on two matrices. Min itself is not Listable, \
so this is what TropicalPlus is for.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0014-4000-8000-000000000014"],

Cell["TropicalPlus[{{1, 2}, {3, 4}}, {{5, 0}, {2, 6}}]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0015-4000-8000-000000000015"],

Cell["Element-wise tropical multiplication.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0016-4000-8000-000000000016"],

Cell["TropicalTimes[{1, 5, 2}, {3, 0, 4}]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0017-4000-8000-000000000017"],

Cell["Examples: matrix product", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0018-4000-8000-000000000018"],

Cell["\<\
Tropical dot product of two vectors: Min over k of x[[k]] + y[[k]].\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0019-4000-8000-000000000019"],

Cell["TropicalDot[{1, 2, 3}, {4, 5, 6}]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-001a-4000-8000-00000000001a"],

Cell["\<\
Tropical matrix product of a 3 x 3 symmetric matrix with itself. The (1, 3) \
entry is Min[0+5, 1+2, 5+0] = 3, capturing a length-2 walk shorter than the \
direct 1-3 entry.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-001b-4000-8000-00000000001b"],

Cell["TropicalDot[{{0, 1, 5}, {1, 0, 2}, {5, 2, 0}}, {{0, 1, 5}, {1, 0, 2}, {5, 2, 0}}]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-001c-4000-8000-00000000001c"],

Cell["\<\
The tropical identity matrix (0 on the diagonal, Infinity elsewhere) acts as \
identity under TropicalDot.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-001d-4000-8000-00000000001d"],

Cell["TropicalMatrixPower[{{0, 1, 5}, {1, 0, 2}, {5, 2, 0}}, 0]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-001e-4000-8000-00000000001e"],

Cell["A -> D: the tropical Kleene fixed point", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-001f-4000-8000-00000000001f"],

Cell["\<\
The graph distance matrix D = GraphDistanceMatrix[g] is the tropical Kleene \
fixed point of the cost-adjacency matrix A: zero on the diagonal, edge cost \
on edges, Infinity off-edge. Iterating tropical multiplication, A^otimes(k) \
stabilises at k = diam(g) to D, and D itself is tropical-idempotent (TropicalDot[D, D] = D, the matrix form of the triangle inequality).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0020-4000-8000-000000000020"],

Cell["\<\
Build the cost-adjacency matrix A from a graph G.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0021-4000-8000-000000000021"],

Cell["\<\
costAdjacency[g_Graph] := With[{n = VertexCount[g], adj = Normal @ \
AdjacencyMatrix[g]}, Table[Which[i == j, 0, adj[[i, j]] == 1, 1, True, \
Infinity], {i, n}, {j, n}]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0022-4000-8000-000000000022"],

Cell["\<\
On a 3 x 3 grid: the tropical (diam)-th power of A equals the full distance \
matrix.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0023-4000-8000-000000000023"],

Cell["\<\
With[{g = GridGraph[{3, 3}]}, TropicalMatrixPower[costAdjacency[g], \
GraphDiameter[g]] === GraphDistanceMatrix[g]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0024-4000-8000-000000000024"],

Cell["\<\
Convergence is sharp: at k = diam - 1 the tropical power still disagrees with \
D.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0025-4000-8000-000000000025"],

Cell["\<\
With[{g = GridGraph[{3, 3}]}, TropicalMatrixPower[costAdjacency[g], \
GraphDiameter[g] - 1] === GraphDistanceMatrix[g]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0026-4000-8000-000000000026"],

Cell["\<\
Beyond the diameter, the tropical power is a fixed point: idempotent under \
TropicalDot, the matrix form of the triangle inequality.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0027-4000-8000-000000000027"],

Cell["\<\
With[{D = GraphDistanceMatrix[GridGraph[{3, 3}]]}, TropicalDot[D, D] === D]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0028-4000-8000-000000000028"],

Cell["\<\
Trace the convergence step by step on a small cycle: NestList of \
TropicalDot[#, A] &.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-0029-4000-8000-000000000029"],

Cell["\<\
With[{A = costAdjacency[CycleGraph[6]]}, NestList[TropicalDot[#, A] &, A, \
GraphDiameter[CycleGraph[6]]]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-002a-4000-8000-00000000002a"],

Cell["\<\
On a disconnected graph the tropical fixed point still recovers \
GraphDistanceMatrix, with Infinity entries between components.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-002b-4000-8000-00000000002b"],

Cell["\<\
With[{g = Graph[{1, 2, 3, 4}, {1 <-> 2, 3 <-> 4}]}, \
TropicalMatrixPower[costAdjacency[g], 5] === GraphDistanceMatrix[g]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-002c-4000-8000-00000000002c"],

Cell["The dual usage of \"Tropical\"", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-002d-4000-8000-00000000002d"],

Cell["\<\
\"Tropical\" attaches to two different kinds of objects in the literature, and \
both senses are used in this paclet -- but neither sense lives in R^n_min. \
Sense 1 is min-plus arithmetic on numbers and matrices: TropicalPlus, \
TropicalTimes, TropicalDot, TropicalMatrixPower, the operations documented in \
this guide. Sense 2 is the synthetic graph translation of tropical-convex \
figures: FindTropicalSegment, GeodesicallyConvexQ, TropicalT1Q in \
TropicalPostulates / TropicalPredicates. The naming pattern is systematic: \
\"Tropical + operation-name\" is sense 1 (arithmetic on graph-derived data); \
\"Tropical + figure-name\" is sense 2 (a graph object playing the role of a \
tropical-convex figure).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-002e-4000-8000-00000000002e"],

Cell["See also", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b1c2d3e4-002f-4000-8000-00000000002f"],

